  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\nWhen editing/replying to a message and leaving the chat without finishing and re-entering the chat, the composer is focused and the keyboard appears. It should behave as it does when leaving the chat with an unfinished message (not editing) - not focused. \r\n\r\n\r\nNOTE for the devs, most likely the issue is in the `...chat.composer.effects/use-edit` and `.../use-reply` effects and we need a condition for re-entering the screen.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/21865759/6c0e7137-1686-48eb-8783-6b47ba0382a0\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe input is not focused when re-entering the screen.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nThe input is focused when re-entering the screen.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Start editing/replying to a message\r\n2. Hide the composer\r\n3. Go back to the chat list\r\n4. Re-enter the chat\r\n5. The composer is focused\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly \r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)",
